VAR met_cleaner = false
~ met_cleaner = true
The man who sits down across from you has the stillness of someone paid to make problems stop. "You're holding something over the Syndicate," he says, like a weather report. "Mireille sent me to discuss... loose ends. You can hand it back, you can talk me out of it, or you can find out what I'm for." He sets both hands flat on the table. "Your call. I'm patient. Not infinitely."
* [Come and take it.]
    "There it is." He almost looks relieved. "I did hope you'd be difficult."
    -> END
* [Let's talk.]
    "Mireille said you might. She also said not to let you. We'll see who she pays better."
    -> END
* [I was just leaving.]
    "Were you. Funny how that works." He doesn't move, but the room feels smaller.
    -> END
